<p>With the #metoo movement in general and the recent attention on <a href="https://medium.com/@kristianlum/statistics-we-have-a-problem-304638dc5de5">harassment in statistics, data science, and machine learning</a> in particular, I am reminded of the Brandeis quote that â€œSunlight is said to be the best of disinfectants.â€ Of course, this is only true if people believe the stories that are voiced, but we seem to be at a watershed moment. I regret not shining more light on this at the time, and hope that we can be more open about violations of community norms, even if they seem â€œminor.â€ They could be indicative of a larger pattern.</p>
